"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-news-news-world-seine-swimming-parisian-tradition-resurrected-for-olympics-with-mayor-taking-a-dip\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbNews\\u00bbWorld  ByAgence France Presse  4 minute read  17 July 2024  09:00 pm  Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo swims in the Seine, in Paris on July 17, 2024, to demonstrate that the river is clean enough to host the outdoor swimming events at the Paris Olympics later this month.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 80, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 92, \"end\": 104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 118, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 128, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6049579349878295e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Despite an investment of 1.4 billion euros ($1.5 billion) to prevent sewage leaks into the waterway, the Seine has been causing suspense in the run-up to the opening of the Paris Games on July 26 after repeatedly failing water quality tests.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 381, \"end\": 386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But since the beginning of July, with heavy rains finally giving way to sunnier weather, samples have shown the river to be ready for the open-water swimming and triathlon - and for 65-year-old Hidalgo.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"score\": 0.9999999996180122, \"rank\": 3.8185059637845466e-10, \"text\": \"Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miguel_Hidalgo_y_Costilla\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by JULIEN DE ROSA / AFP)  Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo took the plunge Wednesday when she jumped into the River Seine in Paris to show the water was clean enough to host Olympic swimming events starting later this month.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 754, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 830, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 845, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6049579349878295e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hidalgo is the latest VIP to cleave through the river's murky waters, after Sports Minister Amelie Oudea-Castera on Saturday.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a major clean-up, many Parisians still recoil at the idea of swimming in a river that regularly tests for high levels of bacteria caused by faecal matter.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:Paris bars to open 24 hours for Olympics opening ceremony  But up until 1923, when it was banned due to pollution and the danger from passing river barges, it was a popular pastime.\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6049579349878295e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is a brief history of Seine swimming:  In the 17th century, before the revolution that toppled France's monarchy, bathing in the Seine was a fashionable pastime - and one that was often conducted naked.\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1530, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999987802401101, \"rank\": 9.286749487973425e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the end of the century, skinny dipping had been outlawed, but Seine swimming remained popular, with floating pools installed along the banks.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most famous of these was the Deligny pool, erected in 1801 on a dozen barges and named after one of the first lifeguards to give bankside swimming lessons.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were some twenty such spots at various points along the river by the end of the 19th century, before they all fell into disuse with the arrival of land-based pools.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some diehards continued to slip on their speedos until the practice was officially banned in 1923.\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even today, a brigade patrols the waters for any divers.\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At times exceptions have been made for Seine swimming, including during heatwaves in the 1940s and official races.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:Blitzboks head to Paris Olympics keen to 'make this one count'  When 5,000 pike were released into the river in 1988, Jacques Chirac as mayor of Paris declared that in five years, Parisians would again be able to swim in the Seine.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2420, \"end\": 2434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2520, \"end\": 2534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Chirac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\"}, {\"begin\": 2547, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6049579349878295e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2627, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will come with towels and antibiotics,\\\" quipped the environment minister at the time, Brice Lalonde.\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chirac repeated his pledge two years later in an interview on French television, adding that he would personally take a public dip in 1993, though he never did before his death in 2019.\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2802, \"end\": 2808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5059028346421518, \"rank\": 0.579936562687314, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CurrentParisMayor Anne Hidalgo revived the dream when bidding for the French capital to get the 2024 Games, promising swimming events in the Seine.\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2945, \"end\": 2957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 2997, \"end\": 3003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5059028346421518, \"rank\": 0.579936562687314, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3068, \"end\": 3073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also added another post-Games goal, to install three summer bathing areas for the general public by the summer of 2025 - one near Notre Dame, another near the Eiffel Tower and a third at Bercy, a quieter neighbourhood in the east.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bercy\", \"score\": 0.9999485163418419, \"rank\": 5.1486308759672196e-05, \"text\": \"Bercy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bercy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bercy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 1.4 billion euros ($1.5 billion) has been invested to make the Seine and its main tributary, the Marne, swimmable, notably by improving waste water collection management.\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3380, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A key feature of the project involved building a massive underground rainwater storage tank near Austerlitz train station to hold excess waste water to ensure it does flow into the Seine.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3586, \"end\": 3596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9999874981203228, \"rank\": 1.2502036170847088e-05, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 3670, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4260606355811267e-22, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has not been all plain sailing.\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last month Hidalgo was forced to call off a swim because of high levels of fecal matter.\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The swimming leg of the Olympics triathlon is set to take place in its waters on July 30-31 and August 5, followed by the open-water swimming on August 8-9.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Agence France-Presse  Add The Citizen as a Preferred Source on Google and follow us on Google News to see more of our trusted reporting in Google News and Top Stories.\", \"from\": 3962, \"to\": 4131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.727058175162701, \"rank\": 0.3753843712294981, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 4051, \"end\": 4062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}, {\"begin\": 4103, \"end\": 4114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Download our app  Get the latest news and updates on Whatsapp  The latest news directly in your inbox  Support Local Journalism  2026 The Citizen.\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4186, \"end\": 4194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Whatsapp\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 4280, \"to\": 4300,